WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:42.259
Welcome to Grade 7 English, Unit 6: Sports, Olympics, and Achievement. Welcome to Unit 6! This unit is all about sports, the Olympics, and what it means to achieve something great. You will explore how athletes train, how the Olympic Games began in ancient Greece, and how the Paralympics have changed our understanding of what the human body can do. Along the way you will build powerful vocabulary, strengthen your grammar, and learn to write about sports with confidence and skill. In this short lecture, preview the key ideas and prepare for the independent lesson.

2
00:00:42.339 --> 00:01:07.662
By the end of this unit, you will be able to read and understand non-fiction texts about sports and the olympic games. you will also use important vocabulary such as analogy, bias, evidence, viewpoint, and more. you will also recognise and form compound nouns (e.g. football, swimming pool, team-mate). Keep these goals in mind as you work.

3
00:01:07.742 --> 00:01:24.152
Your vocabulary work begins with these words: analogy, argumentative, bias, evidence, objective, viewpoint. Listen to each pronunciation in the vocabulary lab, study its meaning in context, and use the word accurately in your own discussion and writing.

4
00:01:24.232 --> 00:01:41.979
The reading sequence includes Sports, Olympics, and Achievement: source text 1 and Sports, Olympics, and Achievement: source text 2. Read actively. Identify each text's central ideas, notice viewpoint and reliability, and support every inference with relevant evidence from the text.

5
00:01:42.059 --> 00:02:09.165
The first language focus is Compound Nouns. What is a compound noun? A compound noun is made by combining two or more words to create a new noun with a specific meaning. Understanding compound nouns helps you express yourself precisely and makes your writing richer. Notice the structure in the model examples, then apply it deliberately in connected sentences and paragraphs.

6
00:02:09.245 --> 00:02:25.209
In speaking, you will complete Speaking 1: Sports Debate. Organise your ideas, use evidence and respond clearly to questions. In writing, you will plan, draft, check and revise. Use the success criteria before submitting your work.

7
00:02:25.289 --> 00:02:43.481
You are ready to begin. Start with the vocabulary lab, continue through reading and comprehension, apply the grammar focus, and complete the speaking and writing practices. Use AI English for hints and feedback, and bring your questions to the live sessions.
